{% from "components/avatar-group/macro.njk" import avatarGroup %}
{% from "components/avatar/macro.njk" import avatar %}
{% from "components/avatar-text/macro.njk" import avatarText %}

<h2>Care team</h2>
{% call avatarGroup({ label: "Care team — 3 members" }) %}
  {% call avatar({ label: "Dr Patel" }) %}{{ avatarText({ text: "DP" }) }}{% endcall %}
  {% call avatar({ label: "Nurse Ahmed" }) %}{{ avatarText({ text: "NA" }) }}{% endcall %}
  {% call avatar({ label: "Dr Smith" }) %}{{ avatarText({ text: "DS" }) }}{% endcall %}
{% endcall %}

<h2>Stacked with overlap</h2>
<p>The example CSS overlaps group members by −0.5rem per avatar
  with a 2px white border, so the stack reads as a cohesive
  collection.</p>
